messages.content:
@everyone 

This channel will be used to announce big and small things related to the project, mute it if you prefer that

first, 2 new user apps:
- iterm - Qt terminal that works great, better than xorg alternatives, + gomuks cli matrix client works on it
- nachat - a Qt matrix client, ancient but usable, its better than gomuks because images, files, scroll bar etc.

as always, downloadable here:
https://github.com/Kobo-InkBox/user-applications

Also, soon will be an annoucement relating kobo nia model c, the incompatible one. We have already a working image of inkbox where only battery level / sleep button doesnt work. If someone wants to test further i can send the image. In 2 weeks it should be fully supported

https://photos.app.goo.gl/Xgq6vpQbFuuF9HCe7
I know it is two general pings in one day but I think a lot of you were waiting for this since a long time

@everyone 
New user app, downloadable here as always: https://github.com/Kobo-InkBox/user-applications

**Syncthing**
from the description: 
Syncthing is a continuous file synchronization program. It synchronizes files between two or more computers in real time, safely protected from prying eyes. Your data is your data alone and you deserve to choose where it is stored, whether it is shared with some third party, and how it’s transmitted over the internet.

Really cool to sync your new books, backup your ereader progress, make your ereader a backup server for small things ;)

Also small note to nachat: It requires above 2.0 gui-bundle, if someone wants it i can provide it, otherwise the app won't launch

Oh and i forgot to mention:
- dont turn on dark mode - the kernel will panick ( this will be redesigned for 2.1 so don't worry )
- xorg is unstable sometimes

@everyone 
I have released a beta image for the Clara HD; read the following MobileRead post for details: https://www.mobileread.com/forums/showpost.php?p=4387514&postcount=102
Feel free to post your thoughts and impressions here!
Enjoy!
